01:39:44,243 --> 01:39:47,007
By looking deep into her eyes?

973
01:39:49,649 --> 01:39:52,049
So you even get jealous, do you?

974
01:39:52,952 --> 01:39:55,045
Only those in love
will feel jealous

975
01:39:55,521 --> 01:40:00,652
I wasn't jealous when you clung
to Shekhar in Switzerland

976
01:40:02,295 --> 01:40:09,064
Sam, please don't remind me of that.
I want to forget it

977
01:40:11,237 --> 01:40:13,330
And what do you want to remember?

978
01:40:18,044 --> 01:40:24,176
This ring. It gave the true love
I always looked for

979
01:40:24,817 --> 01:40:27,479
For which I traveled here
from India

980
01:40:28,521 --> 01:40:32,981
And your journey is over?
- No. It will now begin

981
01:41:29,215 --> 01:41:33,481
"O companion for the night..."

982
01:41:33,819 --> 01:41:38,017
"where are we going?"

983
01:41:38,424 --> 01:41:47,799
"The dawn of love
is about to arrive"

984
01:41:48,134 --> 01:41:57,270
"With the dazzling light
of beauty ahead..."

985
01:41:57,610 --> 01:42:07,212
"dawn is turning away"

986
01:42:30,309 --> 01:42:34,837
"Those asleep, we must awaken"

987
01:42:35,181 --> 01:42:39,208
"Those awake, we must put to sleep"

988
01:42:39,518 --> 01:42:43,921
"To keep us awake..."

989
01:42:44,290 --> 01:42:48,556
"To keep us awake..."

990
01:42:48,894 --> 01:42:53,627
"dawn sings a beautiful lullaby"

991
01:42:53,933 --> 01:42:58,029
"O companion for the night..."

992
01:42:58,337 --> 01:43:02,296
"we're tired, we're headed home"

993
01:43:02,742 --> 01:43:12,117
"The dawn of love
is about to arrive"

994
01:43:12,418 --> 01:43:21,417
"With the dazzling light
of beauty ahead..."

995
01:43:21,761 --> 01:43:30,999
"dawn is turning away"

996
01:43:59,131 --> 01:44:03,568
"Goblets of passion,
the night gave us"

997
01:44:03,903 --> 01:44:08,272
"You and I are drunk
on each other's eyes"

998
01:44:08,541 --> 01:44:12,841
"Our senses haven't
yet been restored..."

999
01:44:13,446 --> 01:44:17,746
"Our senses haven't
yet been restored..."

1000
01:44:18,017 --> 01:44:22,647
"so what else does
the dawn of love offer us?"

1001
01:44:22,955 --> 01:44:26,891
"O companion..."

1002
01:44:27,159 --> 01:44:31,459
"where are we going?"

1003
01:44:31,797 --> 01:44:41,104
"The dawn of love
is about to arrive"

1004
01:44:41,440 --> 01:44:50,439
"With the dazzling light
of beauty ahead..."

1005
01:44:50,816 --> 01:44:59,986
"dawn is turning away"

1006
01:45:23,582 --> 01:45:28,451
"What promises did we make?
What did we swear by?"

1007
01:45:28,721 --> 01:45:32,657
"On a new path,
we have now embarked"

1008
01:45:32,958 --> 01:45:37,190
"No matter how much
we hide our love..."

1009
01:45:37,596 --> 01:45:41,896
"No matter how much
we hide our love..."

1010
01:45:42,201 --> 01:45:46,729
"the dawn of love
knows it all"

1011
01:45:47,039 --> 01:45:51,203
"O beloved..."

1012
01:45:51,544 --> 01:45:55,810
"we're tired. We're going home"

1013
01:45:56,148 --> 01:46:01,313
"The dawn of love..."

1014
01:46:25,570 --> 01:46:27,765
Tired?
- No

1015
01:46:29,240 --> 01:46:31,970
Feeling sleepy?
- No

1016
01:46:34,045 --> 01:46:39,950
Paris is a strange place. You never
know when it's day or night

1017
01:46:40,618 --> 01:46:42,176
And you also don't know
when you fall in love

1018
01:46:46,024 --> 01:46:48,686
Guess what people here do
when they fall in love?

1019
01:46:49,394 --> 01:46:52,886
What?
- They have French onion soup

1020
01:47:02,640 --> 01:47:05,234
You're with Deepa?

1021
01:47:06,211 --> 01:47:08,839
You've conned me to
have her for yourself

1022
01:47:09,147 --> 01:47:12,378
I'm angry with you. You are
no longer my Indian friend!

1023
01:47:13,985 --> 01:47:17,318
Indian friend?
- A liar and a betrayer!

1024
01:47:18,323 --> 01:47:22,817
But he's a Frenchman
- I'm French. He's Indian!

1025
01:47:23,261 --> 01:47:25,092
What does that mean?
- He's lying

1026
01:47:25,630 --> 01:47:28,827
Am I really? You're the liar!
Look at his passport!

1027
01:47:28,933 --> 01:47:29,922
Take a look

1028
01:47:31,936 --> 01:47:37,568
Shyam Kumar, Lucknow, India

1029
01:47:38,576 --> 01:47:42,512
Shyam Kumar alias Mr. Sam,
alias the fake Frenchman!

1030
01:47:42,847 --> 01:47:46,146
Liar, cheat, betrayer!
- How have I deceived you?

1031
01:47:46,551 --> 01:47:49,145
You've made a fool out of me!
- Not at all. On the contrary...

1032
01:47:49,487 --> 01:47:52,251
I've shown you that Indian boys
are capable of being truly in love

1033
01:47:52,523 --> 01:47:55,083
Shut up! I don't even want
to see your face again!

1034
01:47:56,494 --> 01:48:00,021
You love me, don't you?
- Let me go!

1035
01:48:06,337 --> 01:48:08,771
I'm going to beat you to pulp!

1036
01:49:03,761 --> 01:49:06,229
Deepa has been kidnapped.
You are Deepa now

1037
01:49:07,165 --> 01:49:10,134
Till her father arrives,
nobody must get suspicious

1038
01:49:10,535 --> 01:49:15,097
They won't.
But I'm only afraid of Sam

1039
01:49:15,473 --> 01:49:18,442
Sam? He's blinded.
- What?

1040
01:49:18,710 --> 01:49:22,168
Blinded by love. You can easily
lead him up the path

1041
01:49:22,547 --> 01:49:25,380
Besides, you know what Deepa
and he were up to anyway

1042
01:49:43,468 --> 01:49:46,835
Are you okay?
- What's the police for?

1043
01:49:48,439 --> 01:49:52,205
I got a call at the office
telling me that...

1044
01:49:52,510 --> 01:49:53,977
that someone called Jack
has kidnapped you

1045
01:49:54,345 --> 01:49:57,075
He asked for a ransom of a million
dollars for your safe return

1046
01:49:58,616 --> 01:50:01,983
Is that all? Only a million?
- This is no time for jokes

1047
01:50:02,353 --> 01:50:06,187
The police tell me that Jack is
the most dreaded gangster in Europe

1048
01:50:06,524 --> 01:50:11,427
But he hasn't kidnapped me yet.
So why do we need them?

1049
01:50:17,135 --> 01:50:19,899
You ought to be careful, dear.
I was very scared

1050
01:50:20,238 --> 01:50:22,297
What would I tell your father
if something had happened to you?

1051
01:50:22,573 --> 01:50:26,270
Just don't get worried, uncle.
Go on

1052
01:50:40,491 --> 01:50:43,085
If you could fool my father...

1053
01:50:43,428 --> 01:50:45,828
it's easy to con
Deepa's father

1054
01:50:46,164 --> 01:50:48,598
I have no doubt that we'll
soon be millionaires

1055
01:50:49,700 --> 01:50:52,168
But there's time.
- Just a few days

1056
01:50:52,603 --> 01:50:55,629
It isn't right for me to come here.
I'll be leaving now

1057
01:50:55,907 --> 01:50:57,135
I'll give you a call, if need be

1058
01:51:27,972 --> 01:51:30,566
Who is it?
- Shyam

1059
01:51:30,875 --> 01:51:35,209
Alias Sam. Alias Hukum Pasha.
Alias Deepak Sen.

1060
01:51:35,513 --> 01:51:36,810
It's me

1061
01:51:39,350 --> 01:51:40,248
For me?

1062
01:51:41,118 --> 01:51:45,851
Lovely? You mean, no get out?
- What?

1063
01:51:46,190 --> 01:51:50,320
I thought you'd call me names and be
angry and that I'd have to pacify you

1064
01:51:50,561 --> 01:51:54,429
What for?
- Aren't you angry with me?

1065
01:51:55,733 --> 01:51:58,793
Can I ever be angry with you?
- So what was it yesterday?

1066
01:51:59,103 --> 01:52:01,298
Yesterday? Let's forget about it

1067
01:52:01,706 --> 01:52:03,731
What happened yesterday
is in the past

1068
01:52:04,909 --> 01:52:08,504
Deepa, did you never suspect
that I'm an Indian?

1069
01:52:09,380 --> 01:52:10,312
No

1070
01:52:10,781 --> 01:52:12,544
Know why I had to pretend
to be a Frenchman?

1071
01:52:15,219 --> 01:52:18,620
To prove to you that an Indian
is really capable of loving

1072
01:52:19,924 --> 01:52:21,482
I was convinced long ago

1073
01:52:22,593 --> 01:52:24,288
Ever since I met you

1074
01:52:25,596 --> 01:52:28,793
Are you okay?
- What do you think?

1075
01:52:29,100 --> 01:52:31,125
I'm scared! You never got
so close to me!

1076
01:52:32,003 --> 01:52:33,027
Sit down

1077
01:52:35,907 --> 01:52:39,035
Sam, take me out today

1078
01:52:39,744 --> 01:52:42,178
Sure, I will

1079
01:52:42,813 --> 01:52:45,008
I'll go and get ready

1080
01:52:52,023 --> 01:52:53,081
Who's been here?

1081
01:52:54,358 --> 01:52:55,689
No one

1082
01:52:56,861 --> 01:52:58,158
Whose cigarette is this?

1083
01:52:59,964 --> 01:53:02,262
Oh yes, Uncle was here

1084
01:53:03,267 --> 01:53:05,735
This one is still lit.
- Lit?

1085
01:53:08,239 --> 01:53:10,139
He was here a little while
before you came in

1086
01:53:34,065 --> 01:53:35,157
Why're you stopped here?

1087
01:53:35,733 --> 01:53:37,963
I've got to meet Louis.
He has a darkroom in that house there

1088
01:53:41,472 --> 01:53:42,700
Oh yes

1089
01:53:44,675 --> 01:53:46,905
Strange! Yesterday, you were
angry with me because of him

1090
01:53:47,211 --> 01:53:49,543
And now you speak as if
you don't even know him!

1091
01:53:50,147 --> 01:53:51,409
I don't like that man

1092
01:53:52,283 --> 01:53:55,275
Let's talk about something else.
About you and me

1093
01:53:58,089 --> 01:54:02,822
You've changed a lot in a day.
- How come?

1094
01:54:04,528 --> 01:54:07,053
There's a world of a difference between
the Deepa of yesterday and today

1095
01:54:07,398 --> 01:54:11,232
Yes, there is. And you are
the one who's responsible

1096
01:54:11,869 --> 01:54:13,200
I?

1097
01:54:14,271 --> 01:54:17,729
I love you more than I
loved you yesterday

1098
01:54:19,744 --> 01:54:20,676
Why?

1099
01:54:21,345 --> 01:54:24,041
I was angry yesterday.
And instead of taking offense...

1100
01:54:24,382 --> 01:54:26,714
you brought so many flowers for me.
- Is that why!

1101
01:54:27,018 --> 01:54:29,646
I thought it was the engagement ring...
- Engagement ring?

1102
01:54:32,556 --> 01:54:36,652
Where is it?
- I threw it away in a fit of anger

1103
01:54:37,762 --> 01:54:40,731
Good thing too. It was Sam who
put the ring on you yesterday

1104
01:54:41,098 --> 01:54:43,362
Today, Shyam will do it

1105
01:54:45,336 --> 01:54:46,564
Don't lose this one, okay?

1106
01:54:49,573 --> 01:54:52,542
Remember what I said yesterday?
- I do

1107
01:54:53,177 --> 01:54:56,476
But I'd like to hear it again.
- Just that boy meets girl...

1108
01:54:56,881 --> 01:55:01,284
they fall in love, the boy proposes,
makes her wear the ring...

1109
01:55:01,619 --> 01:55:04,019
and then...
- Then?

1110
01:55:05,690 --> 01:55:08,215
This is where I stopped yesterday.
- Didn't you say...

1111
01:55:08,759 --> 01:55:11,284
there's a world of a difference
between yesterday and today?

1112
01:55:13,631 --> 01:55:15,292
Let there be no distance today

1113
01:55:15,733 --> 01:55:19,225
Let the sky and the earth meet

1114
01:55:26,444 --> 01:55:27,741
What happened?

1115
01:55:28,145 --> 01:55:32,912
We're Indians. We don't do
these things before marriage

1116
01:55:46,964 --> 01:55:49,023
Come, let's go

1117
01:55:55,406 --> 01:55:58,307
Damodar...
- Sethji! You?

1118
01:55:58,642 --> 01:56:00,234
Hello Damodar.
- Hello

1119
01:56:00,945 --> 01:56:03,539
Deepa wasn't at the flat.
So I came here

1120
01:56:03,981 --> 01:56:06,916
What brings you here suddenly?
- You sent me a cable...

1121
01:56:07,218 --> 01:56:08,708
to come over immediately.
And I came over

1122
01:56:09,053 --> 01:56:12,045
I didn't send any cable.
- Didn't you?

1123
01:56:12,523 --> 01:56:14,548
So who sent it?
- I did

1124
01:56:16,927 --> 01:56:19,862
So you sent the cable?
- Yes, sir. In daddy's name

1125
01:56:21,532 --> 01:56:23,591
It was a delicate matter and
I wanted you to be here

1126
01:56:23,901 --> 01:56:28,065
What is the matter?
- I want to marry your daughter

1127
01:56:28,472 --> 01:56:29,336
What?

1128
01:56:29,974 --> 01:56:33,137
We're in love with each other and
Deepa has consented to the wedding

1129
01:56:33,677 --> 01:56:35,542
This is impossible!

1130
01:56:36,347 --> 01:56:39,316
You can ask your daughter.
- I certainly will

1131
01:56:39,717 --> 01:56:42,584
I just can't believe that Deepa
has decided to get married!

1132
01:56:42,920 --> 01:56:47,289
What?
- I was fed up of reasoning with her

1133
01:56:47,691 --> 01:56:52,287
She just didn't approve of anyone.
And if wants to marry Shekhar...

1134
01:56:52,696 --> 01:56:54,926
I'm very happy about it.
- Sethji!

1135
01:56:55,699 --> 01:56:59,396
Shekhar is my son, no doubt.
But worthy of Deepa...

1136
01:56:59,737 --> 01:57:01,602
I can't find a better match!

1137
01:57:02,139 --> 01:57:05,631
Damodar, you have looked after
my business all these years

1138
01:57:06,043 --> 01:57:08,637
Shekhar will now look after it.
Go and make a call, son

1139
01:57:08,946 --> 01:57:11,779
Check whether Deepa has returned.
We must finalize this immediately

1140
01:57:12,082 --> 01:57:15,483
What's the hurry? By tomorrow morning...
- Who knows?

1141
01:57:15,820 --> 01:57:19,551
Deepa might change her mind.
You don't know my daughter, Damodar

1142
01:57:19,857 --> 01:57:22,052
I'll call Deepa over.
- Go ahead. Hurry up

1143
01:57:44,048 --> 01:57:45,948
Suzy?
- Who's this?

1144
01:57:58,796 --> 01:58:00,354
When did you return?
- Right now

1145
01:58:00,664 --> 01:58:05,328
What's up? Your skin is glowing.
And what's this?

1146
01:58:05,936 --> 01:58:07,528
This is an engagement ring

1147
01:58:08,172 --> 01:58:11,232
Thank you, Deepaji.
- What for?

1148
01:58:11,575 --> 01:58:15,011
You left us in Beirut and
it strengthened our love

1149
01:58:15,779 --> 01:58:17,406
Congratulations.
- Thank you

1150
01:58:17,481 --> 01:58:19,813
Where's he?
- Over there

1151
01:58:20,651 --> 01:58:24,018
My line's now engaged, feller.
How about yours?

1152
01:58:24,388 --> 01:58:27,448
Makhan, I've some work with you.
I'll be back, Deepa

1153
01:58:27,858 --> 01:58:31,055
Come back soon. We must celebrate
Honey's engagement

1154
01:58:31,428 --> 01:58:33,089
I'll be back, Honey

1155
01:58:37,101 --> 01:58:38,693
Do you know where the
manager's office is?

1156
01:58:39,003 --> 01:58:40,800
Sure, I do.
- Take me there. Quick

1157
01:58:41,105 --> 01:58:41,901
What's wrong?

1158
01:58:43,674 --> 01:58:46,268
Deepa's telephone appears to be dead.
I'll personally go and bring her

1159
01:58:48,279 --> 01:58:49,541
Relax. I'll take it

1160
01:58:53,951 --> 01:58:55,077
Damodar Dayal?

1161
01:58:57,855 --> 01:58:59,117
This is the last warning

1162
01:58:59,623 --> 01:59:02,057
If you still don't agree to pay us
a million dollars...

1163
01:59:02,526 --> 01:59:07,327
Deepa will be finished this evening.
- Finish her

1164
01:59:10,801 --> 01:59:12,792
He's asking us to finish her

1165
01:59:20,144 --> 01:59:21,634
Something is surely wrong
out there

1166
01:59:22,579 --> 01:59:25,047
Leave for Paris immediately and
give me a call from there

1167
01:59:29,019 --> 01:59:33,513
Shekhar... is your daddy in?
- Yes. What happened?

1168
01:59:33,824 --> 01:59:37,521
Can't tell you. Deepa's...
- Makhan Singh. Let's go.

1169
01:59:45,836 --> 01:59:49,101
What?
- The girl in your flat is not Deepa

1170
01:59:49,473 --> 01:59:53,170
But she looks just like Deepa.
As if she were a twin

1171
01:59:55,179 --> 01:59:58,171
Twin?
- Had I not known your daughter well...

1172
01:59:58,482 --> 01:59:59,915
I'd have been deceived too

1173
02:00:05,589 --> 02:00:09,855
Damodar! Could Roopa still
possibly be alive?

1174
02:00:10,427 --> 02:00:13,260
Roopa? Who's that?

1175
02:00:13,630 --> 02:00:20,832
Deepa's twin sister.
Twenty years ago, after my wife died...

1176
02:00:22,006 --> 02:00:26,409
I came to Europe with
both my daughters

1177
02:00:28,045 --> 02:00:32,175
I found an Indian servant
to look after them

1178
02:00:32,716 --> 02:00:38,518
But I didn't know that he was
a gambler and a drunkard

1179
02:00:39,156 --> 02:00:40,384
One evening...

1180
02:00:45,662 --> 02:00:49,723
Jaggu! Where've you been all day?
- I was held up somewhere

1181
02:00:50,067 --> 02:00:54,265
Jaggu! You're drunk!
- I've had a little

1182
02:00:54,538 --> 02:00:57,063
I've hired you to take care
of my children, Jaggu

1183
02:00:59,076 --> 02:01:01,510
It's not for you to go berserk.
- Don't bully me, mister

1184
02:01:01,779 --> 02:01:03,747
This is Europe. It isn't India

1185
02:01:04,281 --> 02:01:07,876
You could face dangerous consequences
for throwing your weight around

1186
02:01:08,152 --> 02:01:09,949
You're threatening me?
Get out!

1187
02:01:10,454 --> 02:01:12,854
Settle my accounts, mister.
Right now

1188
02:01:17,127 --> 02:01:21,063
Mister, you're going to regret this

1189
02:01:32,209 --> 02:01:35,406
That very night, when both
my daughters were asleep...

1190
02:01:36,447 --> 02:01:41,475
I couldn't go to sleep
and was reading a book

1191
02:01:42,386 --> 02:01:44,411
I suddenly heard a scream

1192
02:01:50,094 --> 02:01:51,994
Jaggu! Wait there!

1193
02:01:58,669 --> 02:02:02,571
Deepa was saved. But there was
no trace of Roopa and Jaggu

1194
02:02:02,873 --> 02:02:05,774
One moment...
I've heard the name Jaggu before

1195
02:02:06,477 --> 02:02:09,503
In Switzerland!
When you called Shekhar

1196
02:02:10,447 --> 02:02:15,749
Manager, where's your son right now?
- My son? I don't know. Why ask?

1197
02:02:16,053 --> 02:02:17,452
He knows a thug called Jaggu.

1198
02:02:19,323 --> 02:02:22,724
Jaggu's boss is someone called Jack.
- Jack?

1199
02:02:24,228 --> 02:02:25,923
Jack threatened me over the phone

1200
02:02:26,630 --> 02:02:29,030
Jaggu and Roopa!
After all these years!

1201
02:02:29,433 --> 02:02:32,493
What's happening here?
- I'm baffled too

1202
02:02:32,970 --> 02:02:37,464
If the girl I spoke to at
Deepa's place isn't Deepa...

1203
02:02:37,774 --> 02:02:40,368
It's Roopa then!
It can't be anybody else!

1204
02:02:40,811 --> 02:02:44,406
God has saved her for me!
- Only she knows where Deepa is

1205
02:02:44,748 --> 02:02:45,612
Yes!

1206
02:02:46,783 --> 02:02:48,273
We must go and
meet her right now

1207
02:03:00,297 --> 02:03:02,492
Who's that?
- This is Deepa here

1208
02:03:02,799 --> 02:03:05,029
Suzy, take the back door and
come downstairs immediately

1209
02:03:05,302 --> 02:03:06,132
Why?

1210
02:03:06,503 --> 02:03:08,698
I'll explain later.
Just get out of there. Quick!

1211
02:03:09,072 --> 02:03:09,902
But...

1212
02:03:11,208 --> 02:03:13,073
Makhan Singh, wait here

1213
02:03:13,510 --> 02:03:14,534
Call me later

1214
02:03:29,693 --> 02:03:31,183
Do you know him, Deepa?

1215
02:03:34,231 --> 02:03:37,223
My father. He wanted to meet you
before we get married

1216
02:03:38,168 --> 02:03:39,192
Greetings

1217
02:03:43,907 --> 02:03:45,704
I'm Deepa.
- A fake Deepa

1218
02:03:47,945 --> 02:03:50,470
Because he's the
real Deepa's father

1219
02:03:51,949 --> 02:03:54,577
But you just said...

1220
02:03:54,818 --> 02:03:56,479
I had to prove that
you are not Deepa

1221
02:03:56,820 --> 02:04:00,415
So who am I?
- My lost daughter. Roopa

1222
02:04:00,824 --> 02:04:02,189
Deepa's twin sister

1223
02:04:03,794 --> 02:04:08,629
I'm sorry, but you're
making a mistake

1224
02:04:09,333 --> 02:04:13,360
Mother, father, brothers and sisters
are words alien to me

1225
02:04:13,837 --> 02:04:17,273
